[1/30] [Synthetic Bank] English Primary 5 — QS6  Primary 5  (12.0s)
============================================================
STEM: The weather was very cold ___ we decided to stay indoors.
  (1) because
  (2) so
  (3) but
  (4) or
ANSWER: (2)

ELABORATION (491 chars):
This question tests your understanding of **conjunctions of cause and effect**.

Option **(2) so** is correct because it introduces a **result**. The cold weather is the **cause**, and the **result** is that you decided to stay indoors!

Here is why the other options fail:
**(1) because** introduces a **cause** or reason, not a **result**.
**(3) but** introduces a **contrast**, which does not fit the context of the sentence.
**(4) or** introduces a **choice**, which makes no sense here.

