[2/30] [Synthetic Bank] English Primary 5 — QS7  Primary 5  (11.5s)
============================================================
STEM: Either the parents or their child ___ forgotten to lock the door before leaving.
  (1) have
  (2) did
  (3) has
  (4) will
ANSWER: (3)

ELABORATION (616 chars):
This question tests **Subject-Verb Agreement** when using "either... or...".

When two subjects are joined by "either... or...", the verb must agree with the closest subject. The closest subject here is "child", which is a **singular subject**, so we use the singular helping verb **"has"** to pair with the **past participle** "forgotten".

**(1)** fails because **"have"** is a **plural verb**, but "child" is singular.
**(2)** fails because the helping verb **"did"** requires a **base verb** ("forget"), not "forgotten".
**(4)** fails because the modal verb **"will"** also requires the **base verb** ("forget").

