============================================================
STEM: Neither the principal nor the teachers ___ aware of the sudden change in schedule.
  (1) was
  (2) is
  (3) were
  (4) has been
ANSWER: (3)

ELABORATION (607 chars):
The rule being tested is **subject-verb agreement** using the paired words **"neither... nor"**.

When you use **"neither... nor"**, the verb must agree with the subject closest to it! Since the closest subject, **"teachers"**, is **plural**, we need the **plural verb "were"** to make the sentence correct.

Here is why the other choices fail:
**(1) was**: This is a **singular verb**, so it has a mismatched subject.
**(2) is**: This is also a **singular verb**, so it does not match the **plural** subject.
**(4) has been**: This uses a **singular verb** ("has"), which mismatches the **plural** subject.

