============================================================
STEM: The most exciting adventure John had last year was ___ a new hiking trail in the mountains.
  (1) (1) hikes
  (2) (2) hiking
  (3) (3) hiked
  (4) (4) hike
ANSWER: (2)

ELABORATION (606 chars):
This question tests your knowledge of **gerunds as subject complements**.

After the "be" verb "was", we need a noun to describe John's adventure. Adding "-ing" to an action turns it into a noun called a **gerund**, making **(2) hiking** the perfect fit!

Here is why the other options fail:
- **(1) hikes** is a **present tense verb**, which clashes with the past tense verb "was".
- **(3) hiked** creates the **passive voice** ("was hiked"), which incorrectly means the adventure itself was walked on.
- **(4) hike** is a **base form verb**, which cannot directly follow "was" in this sentence structure.

