  (1) (1) which
  (2) (2) whom
  (3) (3) who
  (4) (4) whose
ANSWER: (4)

ELABORATION (642 chars):
This question tests your knowledge of **relative pronouns** used to show possession or ownership.

Option **(4)** is correct because **"whose"** shows that the broken windows belong to the old house. We use **"whose"** for both people and things to connect a noun to what it owns.

Here is why the other options are incorrect:
Option **(1)** lacks possession; **"which"** refers to things but cannot show ownership directly before a noun.
Option **(2)** uses a mismatched pronoun; **"whom"** is an object pronoun used only for people.
Option **(3)** uses a mismatched pronoun; **"who"** is a subject pronoun used only for people, not a house.

