STEM: Not only _____  Sarah  _____ the race, but she also broke the school record.
  (1) (1) did ... win
  (2) (2) does ... win
  (3) (3) is ... winning
  (4) (4) was ... winning
ANSWER: (1)

ELABORATION (682 chars):
This question tests **negative inversion** and **tense consistency**.

When a sentence starts with a negative phrase like "Not only", we swap the subject and helping verb. Also, since Sarah "broke" the record in the past, the first action must be in the past tense too! Option **(1)** correctly uses the past tense helping verb "did" with the base verb "win".

Here is why the other options fail:
Option **(2)** uses the **wrong tense** because "does" is present tense.
Option **(3)** uses the **wrong tense** because "is winning" is present continuous.
Option **(4)** uses the **wrong tense** because "was winning" is past continuous, which does not fit this completed past action.

