STEM: Halim passed the cookies to Daniel, Aisha and ___.
  (1) I
  (2) me
  (3) mine
  (4) myself
ANSWER: (2)

ELABORATION (726 chars):
This question tests your knowledge of **object pronouns** after a preposition. 

The preposition "to" needs an **object pronoun** to show who receives the action. Since Halim is doing the passing and you are receiving the cookies, the correct answer is **(2)** "me". (Tip: Cross out the other names and read the sentence as "Halim passed the cookies to me"!)

Here is why the other options fail:
**(1)** "I" is a **subject pronoun** used when you are doing the action, not receiving it.
**(3)** "mine" is a **possessive pronoun** showing ownership, which does not fit the sentence structure.
**(4)** "myself" is a **reflexive pronoun**, which is only used when the person doing the action and receiving it are the same person.

