  (1) will get
  (2) would get
  (3) will have gotten
  (4) would have gotten
ANSWER: (4)

ELABORATION (536 chars):
This question tests **Third Conditional sentences**, which talk about an unreal event in the past.

Because the "if" part uses the **past perfect tense** ("had rained"), the main part must use "**would have**" plus a **past participle** ("gotten"). This makes **(4)** correct!

**(1)** uses the **future tense**, which is used for real future possibilities.
**(2)** uses the **present conditional**, which is used for imaginary present situations.
**(3)** uses the **future perfect tense**, which does not match a past unreal condition.

